    "137221058": {
      "title": "Subsurface Zone in Pure Magnesium Studied by Positron Lifetime Spectroscopy",
      "abstract": "This paper presents the results of investigation of a subsurface zone created during dry sliding in pure magnesium. Positronannihilation and microhardness techniques were used to detect the defect distribution below the worn surface. Near to the surfacethere was found a strong gradient of dislocations and defects associated with them, which were extended more than a hundred ofmicrometers. The decrease of microhardness at a depth less than 30 lm from a worn surface suggested that dynamic recovery tookplace in pure magnesium. The defect proﬁles were also studied for samples exposed to compression and blasting.KEY WORDS: subsurface zone, positron annihilation, defect depth proﬁle, magnesium"
    }
  },
